{{lang|zh|枼}} and characters derived from it represent the phonetic series *''lep'' with the root meanings of “flat, wide, thin”. Members from this word family possibly include:
* {{och-l|葉|leaf}}
* {{och-l|鰈|flatfish, plaice}}
* {{och-l|楪}} > {{och-l|碟|plate}}
* {{och-l|牒|official document < plank}}.
* {{och-l|蝶|butterfly}} > {{och-l|蝴蝶|tr=*ɡaː l'eːb}}

Compare with the Middle Korean:
* {{m|ko|나븨|t=butterfly|pos=modern {{m|ko|나비}}}}
* {{m|ko|닢|t=leaf|pos=modern {{m|ko|잎}}}}
* {{m|ko|넙치|t=flatfish}},

These are likewise derived from the similarly shaped adjective root {{m|ko|넙다|tr=nep-|t=to be wide, flat|pos=modern {{m|ko|넓다|tr=neol(p)-}}}}.

See {{zh-l|蝴蝶}} for more information.
